  "translations": {
    "en": "Know you, O slaves of Allah! Your weak spirits and your delicate bodies, for which little discomfort is enough to break down, will be terribly weakened because of this. So if you can have mercy over your bodies and spirits by saving them from what they cannot bear, then act according to what Allah likes, and discard what He dislikes.",
    "ur": "Know you, O slaves of Allah! Your weak spirits and your delicate bodies, for which little discomfort is enough to break down, will be terribly weakened because of this. So if you can have mercy over your bodies and spirits by saving them from what they cannot bear, then act according to what Allah likes, and discard what He dislikes.",
